<task id="configure-berkeley-datasource">
    <title>How to Configure a Berkeley DB XML Data Source</title>
  <!--Proofed-->
    <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Native XML Databases (NXD)<indexterm>data sources configuration<indexterm>Berkeley DB
              XML</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p><ph keyref="product"/> supports Berkeley DB XML versions <ph
          keyref="berkeleyVersions"/>. The steps for configuring a data source for a Berkeley DB XML
        database are as follows:</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step id="step1">
        <cmd><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusables-working-with-databases.dita#reusables-working-with-databases/open-ds"
          /></cmd>
      </step>
            <step>
        <cmd><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusables-working-with-databases.dita#reusables-working-with-databases/click-new"
          /></cmd>
      </step>
            <step id="step3">
        <cmd><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusables-working-with-databases.dita#reusables-working-with-databases/unique-name"
          /></cmd>
      </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select <i>Berkeley DBXML</i> from the driver <uicontrol>Type</uicontrol>
                  drop-down menu.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Add</uicontrol> button to add the Berkeley DB driver
          files. </cmd>
                <info>
                    <p>The driver files for the Berkeley DB database are the following:</p>
                    <ul>
                      <li><filepath>db.jar</filepath> (check for it in
                <filepath>[DBXML_DIR]/lib</filepath> or <filepath>[DBXML_DIR]/jar</filepath>)</li>
                      <li><filepath>dbxml.jar</filepath> (check for it in
                <filepath>[DBXML_DIR]/lib</filepath> or <filepath>[DBXML_DIR]/jar</filepath>)</li>
                    </ul>
                  <p>Where <filepath>[DBXML_DIR]</filepath> is the Berkeley DB XML database root
            directory. For example, in Windows it is: <filepath>C:\Program Files\Oracle\Berkeley DB
              XML &lt;version></filepath>.</p>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step6">
                <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol> button to finish the data source
                    configuration.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
